<h3>Lab Assignment:</h3>

Note: Everything in this lab assignment, unless otherwise stated, must be performed on the <span style="font-variant: small-caps;">csci2</span> server.

<ol TYPE=I>

    <li>
	Using the Unix command, <code>mkdir</code>, create the directory <code>labs</code> in your home directory.
    </li>

    <li>
    Using the <code>mkdir</code> Unix command, create the directory <code>lab1</code> in your <code>labs</code> directory, then move to it<br>
    (you can use the <code>cd</code> or <code>pushd</code>/<code>popd</code> commands in Unix to move between a directories).
    </li>

    <li>
	Read Gaddis' intro to Unix <a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/8e/Labs/LM_AppendixB.pdf">here</a>
    </li>

    <li>
	Use your editor to write the answers to the questions and exercises in
	<a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/8e/Labs/LM_Chapter01.pdf">Lab 1</a>
	in the file <code>answers.txt</code>
	locating it in directory <code>lab1</code></li> then submit the file to your lab1 dropbox in D2L.<br>
	As with all assignments submitted to a dropbox, the following data must be included at the top of your file:
	<ul>
	    <li> your name </li>
	    <li> your <span style="font-variant: small-caps;">csci2</span> login </li>
	    <li> the assignment category &amp; number [e.g. Lab 1] </li>
	    <li> the submission date </li>
	</ul>
    </li>

</ol>
Here are the authors' source files for this lab:
<ul>
    <li> <a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/7e/Labs/SourceCode/Lab1/firstprog.cpp"><code>firstprog.cpp</code></a></li>
    <li> <a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/7e/Labs/SourceCode/Lab1/semiprob.cpp"><code>semiprob.cpp</code></a></li>
    <li> <a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/7e/Labs/SourceCode/Lab1/runprob.cpp"><code>runprob.cpp</code></a></li>
    <li> <a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/7e/Labs/SourceCode/Lab1/logicprob.cpp"><code>logicprob.cpp</code></a></li>
</ul>

